{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/civil-nuclear-constabulary/about","content_id":"5f67f434-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","description":"The CNC protects civil nuclear sites and nuclear materials in England and Scotland. We also police and protect other, non-nuclear critical infrastructure.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We’re governed by the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-nuclear-police-authority\">Civil Nuclear Police Authority</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>We employ over 1,800 police officers and staff at sites throughout the UK.</p>\n\n<p>Working closely with industry and regulatory stakeholders, we provide armed protective security at each location, maintaining effective relationships with local Home Office forces and Police Scotland.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-responsibilities\">Our responsibilities</h2>\n\n<p>We are responsible for the armed protection of civil nuclear facilities and materials whether they are on site or in transit and protect other, non-nuclear critical national infrastructure. Counter-terrorism is a major part of our policing.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-ambition\">Our ambition</h2>\n\n<p>To be recognised nationally and internationally as the leading policing organisation for the armed protection of civil nuclear material and the critical national infrastructure of the UK.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-mission\">Our mission</h2>\n\n<p>In partnership with the civil nuclear industry, national security agencies and regulatory bodies, the <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> will deter any attacker whose intent is the theft, sabotage or destruction of nuclear material, whether static or in transit, or the sabotage of high consequence facilities. If an attack occurs, <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> will defend that material and those facilities and deny access to them. If material is seized or high consequence facilities are compromised, the <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> will recover control of those facilities and regain custody of the material.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-priorities\">Our priorities</h2>\n\n<p>For 2023 to 2026, our three strategic goals are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain the <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr> core mission and offer its unique capabilities to benefit the wider policing and security infrastructure</li>\n  <li>Enhance the effectiveness and efficiency of the <abbr title=\"Civil Nuclear Constabulary\">CNC</abbr>\n</li>\n  <li>Foster and maintain a unified and inclusive culture which supports an engaged and diverse workforce</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For more information see our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cnpa-three-year-strategic-plan-202427\">Strategic Plan 2024/27</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Or see our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cnc-annual-business-plan-202526\">Annual Business Plan 2025/26</a>.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"Updated to include other, non-nuclear critical infrastructure. ","public_timestamp":"2025-12-19T16:32:30Z"},{"note":"Strategic plan updated. ","public_timestamp":"2025-09-08T10:48:23Z"},{"note":"The Annual Business Plan has been updated with the newest version. ","public_timestamp":"2025-05-02T08:19:43Z"},{"note":"The Our mission section has been amended. ","public_timestamp":"2024-01-05T16:01:24Z"},{"note":"Annual business plan added. ","public_timestamp":"2023-12-22T12:34:47Z"},{"note":"Ambition changed and updated. Three year strategic plan updated. ","public_timestamp":"2023-06-22T11:02:00Z"},{"note":"Updated with latest strategy","public_timestamp":"2021-12-13T11:40:49Z"},{"note":"Priorities updated and link to new business strategy added.","public_timestamp":"2017-07-28T10:10:15Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2014-07-09T14:56:38Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":["5fa9d419-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","5f65b2